article.headline: N. Arizona 44, Portland St. 23
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Michael Herrick passed for 254 yards and three touchdowns to lead Northern Arizona to a convincing 44-23 victory over Portland State in Big Sky Conference action on Saturday. Northern Arizona (4-2, 3-1) led almost the entire way. Herrick entered the contest as the Big Sky?s top-ranked passer and he was rarely pressured by a Portland State defense that has allowed more than 400 yards per game. Herrick completed 21 of 34 attempts and connected with Conrad Meadows for a pair of scores, including a 31-yarder that gave the Lumberjacks a 30-9 lead late in the third quarter. Portland State (2-5, 1-4), which was playing without injured first-string quarterback Drew Hubel, didn't score a touchdown until backup quarterback Connor Cavanaugh's 7-yard run early in the fourth period cut Northern Arizona?s lead to 30-16.
